issue.title: tests hanging
issue.body:
MacOS 10.15.6, Xcode-11.7, current master.

Build seems to succeed, `test_kem` and `speed_kem` appear to work fine.

Tests hang regardless of what flags CMake receives.

issue.title: Update Doxyfile to match the current sources
issue.body:
In short:
```diff
diff --git a/docs/.Doxyfile b/docs/.Doxyfile
index d162651a..b42ee8bf 100644
--- a/docs/.Doxyfile
+++ b/docs/.Doxyfile
@@ -792,9 +792,9 @@ WARN_LOGFILE           =
 # Note: If this tag is empty the current directory is searched.
 
 INPUT                  = src/common/common.h \
-                         src/common/rand.h \
-                         src/crypto/sha2/sha2.h \
-                         src/crypto/sha3/sha3.h \
+                         src/common/rand/rand.h \
+                         src/common/sha2/sha2.h \
+                         src/common/sha3/sha3.h \
                          src/kem/kem.h \
                          src/sig/sig.h \
                          README.md
@@ -2139,7 +2139,7 @@ TAGFILES               =
 # tag file that is based on the input files it reads. See section "Linking to
 # external documentation" for more information about the usage of tag files.
 
-GENERATE_TAGFILE       = NO
+#GENERATE_TAGFILE       = NO
 
 # If the ALLEXTERNALS tag is set to YES, all external class will be listed in
 # the class index. If set to NO, only the inherited external classes will be
```
Reason - `doxygen` v1.8.20 and newer require that `GENERATE_TAGFILE = filename`. It does not accept `NO`.


If you also do 
```
$ doxygen -u docs/.Doxyfile
```
it would be nice - but if not, users can do that on their own.

comment.body: Thanks. This was actually already being done as part of #817 but it's been held up by other changes, so I've pulled it out into a separate PR to be merged sooner.

```bash
env RUN_TESTS_PARALLEL=FALSE cmake -GNinja ..
ninja
ninja run_tests
```

issue.title: Fix appveyor test failures
issue.body: Appveyor installed a newer version of MSVC (from 19.26.28806.0 to 19.27.29111.0), which resulted in failures on the nightly build. This PR tweaks the picnic include files to accommodate this change.

comment.body:
> > Rebase off of master once #822 lands and that should resolve the Doxygen failure in the macOS-shared-openssl build.
> 
> We might have a little chicken and egg problem here: it looks like #822 is blocked by the appveyor failure that this PR fixes. Perhaps we should include this commit in the other PR.

Okay, if the CI on the other PR passes except for AppVeyor, I'll cherry pick this over to that PR.
